lead_paragraph: Several thousand pelicans have died in the past month at a California wildlife reserve, and scientists now believe that the killer is avian botulism caused by eating infected fish. Since Aug. 15, 6,266 pelicans have died at the Salton Sea National Wildlife Refuge, about 150 miles east of San Diego. In all, 8,672 birds of 51 species have died in the refuge in that time.
